http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Coast-Guard-host-special-children-on-ships/article13995152.ece

Ahead of its raising day on February 1, the Coast Guard hosted special children on board its ships Varuna and Abhinav on Monday.Nearly 50 students and two teachers from ‘Snehalayam’, Kakkanad, were taken aboard the vessels where they interacted with Coast Guard personnel.In a conducted tour, they were shown various equipments fitted on the vessels. A magic show was also organised by the Coast Guard District Headquarters No. 4 with jurisdiction over Kerala and Mahe to entertain the schoolchildren.